Shaft completely lined with brick. This and the next tomb (206) seem to have been constructed together. A square pit was dug and lined with brick and the chambers were arched and the pits divided and then the whole filled in. (but see plan for description of construction.) The rubbish throughout the shaft was filled with numerous rough offering pots. A few feet from the ground in the rubbish were found a shallow red glazed bowl, and a single green glass bead and a small uzat eye were found in the rubbish near the [...] of the chamber set app. 3'0" from the ground. On the ground of the shaft was a single leg of an ox. In the chamber was some 6" of coffin and human bones scattered about promiscuously. The chamber had been sealed in the same way as F.206. A few rough pots had penetrated into the chamber.
Numerous rough pots in rubbish of shaft.

Door originally closed with bricks plastered with mud outside flush with the face of the shaft. The shaft was entirely lined with bricks and the chamber arched.
